programme.desc: Crystal Palace v Watford. Action from the 2012/13 Championship play-off final at Wembley Stadium, as the teams contested a place in the top flight alongside the already promoted Cardiff City and Hull City. Palace reached this match when Wilfried Zaha scored a brace in a 2-0 away win against Brighton & Hove Albion after a goalless draw in the first leg. Meanwhile, Watford bounced back from narrowly missing out on automatic promotion by overcoming Leicester City in dramatic fashion, with Troy Deeney scoring an injury time-winner on the counter after Manuel Almunia had saved a penalty.

programme.desc: Bradford City v Northampton Town. Action from the 2012/13 League Two play-off final at Wembley Stadium, where promotion to League One awaited the winners. The Bantams were making their second appearance of the season at Wembley having also reached the League Cup final following an outstanding giant-killing run, and they needed to come from behind to edge out Burton Albion to reach this stage. The Cobblers ended a run of recent poor form to win 1-0 in both legs of their semi-final against Cheltenham Town to move within one match of reaching the third tier of English football.

programme.desc: With the rut soon to be underway, hunting over mock scrapes can be deadly. Learn as Kyle Wieter shares his techniques on the best locations for using the Scrape Fix System and then getting the intel to be successful through the use of trail cameras.(n)

programme.title: North American Whitetail Television
programme.desc: Stan Potts starts the archery season in style with a western Kentucky bowhunt, Dr. James Kroll kicks off an all-new series on managing small properties, and Pat Hogan talks rangefinder technology.(n)

programme.title: Bowlife
programme.desc: It's early October and the entire Morgan family is hunting the family farm in Ohio. While Levi is busy figuring out a giant nine-point, his dad is wasting no time punching his first tag.(n)

programme.title: Dominant Bucks
programme.desc: Kansas bowhunter Matt Fryer and Massachusetts bowhunter Cory DeSousa find, set up and arrow mature dominant bucks.(n)

programme.title: BuckVentures Outdoors
programme.desc: Part 1. Jeff Danker is in Ohio in pursuit of a 180+ whitetail that he has several years of history with.(n)

programme.title: Bowhunter TV
programme.desc: Team Bowhunter makes its annual pilgrimage to the elk-rich high country of Colorado's Cross Mountain Ranch. Danny Farris talks about the importance of mover sights.(n)

programme.title: Adrenaline
programme.desc: With the rut soon to be underway, hunting over mock scrapes can be deadly. Learn as Kyle Wieter shares his techniques on the best locations for using the Scrape Fix System and then getting the intel to be successful through the use of trail cameras.(n)

programme.title: Gun It With Benny Spies
programme.desc: Benny and his buddies catch walleye and smallmouth bass.(n)

programme.title: Backcountry Hunters TV
programme.desc: Hal Gahm treks the scenic mountains of west Texas and has some close encounters with aoudad.(n)

programme.title: Elk Camp
programme.desc: Part 1. Steve Chappell guides husband and wife team, John and Sally Holzheuter, who have both drawn coveted Arizona elk tags in Unit 9.(n)

programme.title: Wildlifers
programme.desc: Texas country music artist Kevin Fowler joins the WildLifers on a hunt in New Mexico during elk season. Dan Braman arrives to camp just a couple days early and sets out to fill his tag.(n)

programme.title: Petersen's Hunting Adventures
programme.desc: David Draper teams up with Fred Eichler to hunt elk on the high plains of southern Colorado.(n)

programme.title: Extreme Outer Limits TV
programme.desc: Part 1. The team hunts bull elk during Oregon's late season.(n)

programme.title: Whitetail Properties
programme.desc: Dan Perez started the season with the grim reality of having a short hit list this year. Rolling with the punches and keeping close eyes on his trail cameras, he hit a lucky strike. A well-known buck shows back up, and the hunt for Royale is on.(n)

programme.title: Huntin' the Backwoods
programme.desc: Karl and Paul continue their hunt at Koringkoppie Safaris in South Africa. Paul has had an eventful trip and hands the Excalibur Crossbow over to Karl to give him a chance on plains game in Africa.(n)

programme.title: North American Whitetail Television
programme.desc: Stan Potts starts the archery season in style with a western Kentucky bowhunt, Dr. James Kroll kicks off an all-new series on managing small properties, and Pat Hogan talks rangefinder technology.(n)

programme.title: The Ozonics Experience
programme.desc: Ozonics.(n)

programme.title: Greg McHale's Wild Yukon
programme.desc: Greg and Karl search for a late-season dall sheep from the river bottoms to the mountain peaks. Charging hard into the final days of the season, the team must keep it together to end on a high note.(n)

programme.title: Under Wild Skies
programme.desc: Josh Powell takes a team to Broken Bow, Nebraska's one box pheasant hunt. The pressure is on because Tony Makris won the event 25 years ago with a team of his own. Also: quail hunting from the long leaf pine of Georgia.(n)

programme.title: Trijicon's World of Sports Afield
programme.sub-title: Feeding a Passion for Mule Deer
programme.desc: Tim Harold is in hot pursuit of mule deer. The rut is kicking in as Tim joins good friend Tom McReynolds in the great state of South Dakota. This area holds world-class mule deer, but the open country often makes closing the gap for a shot difficult.(n)

programme.title: The Fierce Life
programme.desc: Fierce team member Devin Archibald travels to northern Nevada to hunt mule deer.(n)

programme.title: RNT-V
programme.desc: Jimbo, Blake, Jake and Charlee the duck dog head West to meet up with Ryan Livingston and Prairie Rock Outfitters for some epic Platte River waterfowling.(n)

programme.title: Avian-X TV
programme.desc: Fred and friends hit the duck marsh in November, peak hunting season across the country. Fred overcomes unexpected conditions on his home turf in Ohio when he finds the marsh is not in the condition he left it.(n)

programme.title: Bill Dance Saltwater
programme.desc: Part 1. Anchor fishing in a swift, strong current, Bill Dance and Captain Steve Crowder redfish the St. Johns River.(n)

programme.title: Sweetwater
programme.desc: Miles and Joey look back on their many experiences fishing river systems versus lakes.(n)

programme.title: Respect the Game TV
programme.desc: Shermoe Adventures is a place the RTG team trys to hit every year. Larry McCoy and Tony Glidewell show why it's Iowa's premier outfitters.(n)

programme.title: Razor Dobbs Alive
programme.desc: Razor Dobbs hunts whitetail and blackbuck antelope with the suppressed CZ Scorpion SBR.(n)

programme.title: Out-There TV
programme.sub-title: Kentucky Kids Race to the Woods
programme.desc: The Kentucky Speedway is home to one of the best NASCAR tracks in America. They believe in racing, and they believe in passing down the tradition of hunting. Six lucky kids hit the property during youth season in hopes of filling their tags.(n)

programme.title: Hornady's Dark & Dangerous *
programme.desc: Our hunters are after different game, and hunting in different countries, but they too will experience the unexpected gifts that can fall into a hunters lap in good game country.(n)

programme.title: Gallery of Guns

programme.desc: Ruger's Mark Gurney will present the 10/22 American Eagle TALO Special Edition & the AR-556 MPR. We'll also shoot a very easy to operate .380 from S&W, the M&P Shield EZ. Taurus' Jacob Eaton will be firing rounds through the Raging Hunter revolver.(n)

programme.title: All Things Hunting - ATH
programme.desc: Kyle and Cole spend a season in Oklahoma chasing a buck that seems to have no bounds on his home range. The buck named Sticker-Buck is both elusive and visible through most of the season before a full rut encounter gives them a shot.(n)
